      <h2>Top Attractions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Charminar:</strong> The iconic symbol of Hyderabad, built in 1591.</li>
        <li><strong>Golconda Fort:</strong> A historic fort with a stunning view of the city.</li>
        <li><strong>Hussain Sagar Lake:</strong> A beautiful man-made lake with boat rides and views of the Buddha statue.</li>
        <li><strong>Ramoji Film City:</strong> A popular film studio and tourist destination offering guided tours.</li>
        <li><strong>Salar Jung Museum:</strong> One of the largest museums in India, with a rich collection of artifacts.</li>
        <li><strong>Qutub Shahi Tombs:</strong> A historical site where the Qutub Shahi rulers are buried.</li>
        <li><strong>Chilkur Balaji Temple:</strong> A popular temple dedicated to Lord Venkateswara.</li>
        <li><strong>Laad Bazaar:</strong> A famous market known for its traditional bangles and jewelry.</li>
        <li><strong>Birla Mandir:</strong> A temple built on a hilltop, offering panoramic views of Hyderabad.</li>
        <li><strong>Necklace Road:</strong> A scenic road around Hussain Sagar Lake, perfect for a relaxing stroll.</li>
      </ul>
